Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the layout bug. Let me create a comprehensive report with the full DOM hierarchy and CSS analysis.

## Mobile Layout Bug Analysis: PostCards.jsx

I've thoroughly explored the component and CSS. Here's the complete breakdown:

---

### **1. DOM HIERARCHY (Lines 881-968 of PostCards.jsx)**

```jsx
<div className="card-icons-container">

  {/* ROW 1: Author info + action icons (WRAPPED INTO SINGLE ELEMENT) */}
  <div className="user-info-child-container">

    {/* Avatar */}
    <div className={`user-avatar-container ...`}>
      <img className="user-info-avatar" ... />
    </div>

    {/* Name + Badge */}
    <div className="user-name-container">
      <p className="user-newsfeed-name">{journal.users.name}</p>
      <VerifiedBadge ... />
    </div>

    {/* Separator dot */}
    <div className="name-info-separator">•</div>

    {/* Post date */}
    <p className="user-post-date">{formatPostDate(journal.created_at)}</p>

    {/* ACTION ICONS (NESTED INSIDE user-info-child-container) */}
    {cardIcons && cardIcons.map((icon, index) => (
      <div key={index} className="icon-container">
        {/* like, comment, bookmark, repost, views all go here */}
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  {/* ROW 2: Reading time pill (pushed right) */}
  <div className="reading-time-container">
    <p className="reading-time-text">{CalculateText(wholeText)}</p>
  </div>

  {/* ROW 3: Settings gear menu (pushed right) */}
  <div className="user-post-settings">
    <svg onClick={(e) => handleClickSettings(e, journal.id)} .../>
    {postIdSettings === journal.id && (
      <motion.div className="setting-modal">...</motion.div>
    )}
  </div>
</div>
```

---

### **2. DESKTOP CSS (Lines 312-706)**

```css
/* Card container */
.cards {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    width: 99%;
    background-color: var(--bg-card);
}

/* Card content area (title + text) */
.card-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.8rem;
    width: 100%;
    padding: 1rem 1.15rem 0.6rem 1.15rem;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* Icon bar / footer */
.card-icons-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;              /* ← allows wrapping */
    width: 100%;
    padding: 0.5rem 1.15rem 0.85rem 1.15rem;
    min-height: 22px;
    align-items: center;           /* ← vertical center */
    justify-content: flex-start;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-card);
}

/* User info row (desktop layout) */
.user-info {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
}

/* User info child (avatar + name + date) */
.user-info-child-container {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    height: 100%;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    width: fit-content;
}

/* Reading time pill - pushed right via margin-left: auto */
.reading-time-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.7rem;
    background-color: var(--bg-pill);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-card);
    border-radius: 10px;
    margin-left: auto;             /* ← PUSHES RIGHT ON DESKTOP */
}

.reading-time-text {
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    font-weight: 550;
    color: var(--accent-sage);
}

/* Settings icon */
.user-post-settings {
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-self: flex-end;
    width: fit-content;
    height: fit-content;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: var(--text-heading);
}
```

**Desktop Flow:** All elements are siblings in `.card-icons-container` → flex wrapping allows them to stay on one row with gap spacing → `margin-left: auto` on reading-time-container pushes it right → user-post-settings follows naturally.

---

### **3. MOBILE CSS (Lines 1028-1159)**

```css
@media (max-width: 480px) {

    /* Footer container: forces wrapping */
    .card-icons-container {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        width: 100%;
        padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem 0.7rem 0.75rem;
        min-height: auto;
        height: auto;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: flex-start;
        gap: 0.4rem;
        row-gap: 0.5rem;           /* ← gap between rows */
        box-sizing: border-box;
        overflow: visible;
    }

    /* ⚠️ CRITICAL: Row 1 — author info forced to full width */
    .card-icons-container .user-info-child-container {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        flex: 0 0 100%;             /* ← FORCES FULL WIDTH = AUTO WRAP */
        gap: 0.3rem;
        padding-bottom: 0.25rem;
        border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border-card);
        margin-bottom: 0.1rem;
    }

    /* Truncate name on mobile */
    .card-icons-container .user-info-child-container .user-newsfeed-name {
        font-size: 0.72rem;
        white-space: nowrap;
        overflow: hidden;
        text-overflow: ellipsis;
        max-width: 120px;
    }

    /* Date text size */
    .card-icons-container .user-info-child-container .user-post-date {
        font-size: 0.6rem;
        white-space: nowrap;
    }

    /* Avatar size */
    .card-icons-container .user-info-child-container .user-info-avatar {
        width: 20px;
        height: 20px;
    }

    /* ⚠️ Row 2: Action icons forced visible */
    .icon-container {
        display: flex !important;
        align-items: center;
        flex-shrink: 1;
        min-width: 0;
        min-height: 24px;
        visibility: visible;        /* ← force visible */
    }

    /* Icon buttons */
    .icon-container .like-button,
    .icon-container .comment-button,
    .icon-container .bookmark-button {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        padding: 0.3rem;
        border-radius: 50%;
        transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
    }

    /* SVG icon sizes */
    .svg-like, .svg-comment, .svg-bookmark {
        width: 18px !important;
        height: 18px !important;
        display: block;
    }

    /* ⚠️ Reading time pill — always visible, pushed right */
    .reading-time-container {
        display: flex !important;
        visibility: visible;
        margin-left: auto;          /* ← STILL PUSHED RIGHT */
        padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
        flex-shrink: 0;
        min-width: fit-content;
    }

    .reading-time-text {
        font-size: 0.58rem;
        white-space: nowrap;
    }

    /* Settings button */
    .user-post-settings {
        flex-shrink: 0;
        color: var(--text-heading);
    }

    .user-post-settings svg {
        width: 20px;
        height: 20px;
    }
}
```

---

### **4. THE PROBLEM: Why Elements End Up at Bottom**

**Root Cause:** The `user-info-child-container` has `flex: 0 0 100%` which forces it to take full width on mobile. This causes a hard line break after the author info row. However:

1. **All action icons are nested INSIDE `.user-info-child-container`** (lines 893-946 of JSX)
2. The container doesn't have horizontal scrolling or overflow constraints
3. On mobile, the icons get wrapped but **there's no constraint forcing them onto a second row within the container**

**Secondary Issue:** The CSS uses `flex-wrap: wrap` on `.card-icons-container` BUT:
- The `user-info-child-container` (with `flex: 0 0 100%`) forces a break AFTER itself
- `.reading-time-container` and `.user-post-settings` are siblings of `user-info-child-container`, NOT children
- They appear AFTER the author row in the DOM flow, so they naturally appear below on mobile

**Expected behavior on mobile:**
```
Row 1: [avatar] [name] [date] | [reading-time] [settings]
```

**Actual behavior on mobile:**
```
Row 1: [avatar] [name] [date] ─────────────── (full width)
Row 2: [like] [comment] [bookmark] [repost]   (action icons)
Row 3: [reading-time]                          (alone on right)
Row 4: [settings]                              (alone on right)
```

---

### **5. KEY STRUCTURAL ISSUES**

1. **Architectural Mismatch:** Action icons are nested in `user-info-child-container`, but they should be siblings at the `card-icons-container` level to appear on the same line as reading-time and settings.

2. **CSS Override Conflict:** 
   - Desktop: `align-items: center` + flex-wrapping keeps everything aligned
   - Mobile: `flex: 0 0 100%` forces author row to break, but icons are still children of that container

3. **DOM Structure Problem:**
   ```jsx
   <card-icons-container>  ← flex-wrap parent
     <user-info-child-container flex: 0 0 100%>  ← forces wrap
       ... avatar, name, date, icons (NESTED!)
     </user-info-child-container>
     <reading-time-container>  ← appears AFTER wrap
     <user-post-settings>       ← appears AFTER wrap
   </card-icons-container>
   ```

---

### **6. SUMMARY TABLE**

| Element | Desktop | Mobile | Issue |
|---------|---------|--------|-------|
| `.user-info-child-container` | `flex: auto` (fits content) | `flex: 0 0 100%` (full width) | Breaks layout, icons wrapped |
| `.reading-time-container` | Sibling of user-info, pushed right via `margin-left: auto` | Same CSS but appears AFTER wrap | No longer adjacent to user info |
| `.user-post-settings` | Last sibling, right-aligned | Same but appears LAST | Far from action icons |
| Action icons | Inside `.user-info-child-container`, fit naturally | Same, but wrap to next line within container | Hidden or at bottom of card |

The fix would require restructuring the JSX to move action icons out of `user-info-child-container` and make them direct children of `card-icons-container`.
